0distortions%20indicative%20of%20gravitational%20waves%20using%20three%20distinct%20detectors%20located%20globally.%20The%20most%20recent%20signal%20was%20captured%20by%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year's%20latest%20observation%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20found%20that%20object%20to%20be%20quite%20fascinating%20since%20it%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bmass%20gap%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20means%20that%20its%20mass%20is%20between%202.5%20and%204.5%20times%20that%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fexplained-what-do-scientists-hope-to-learn-from-rare-total-solar-eclipse-5391108%5C%22%3ESun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reports%20the%20Independent.%20The%20range%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bgap%26quot%3B%20is%20between%20the%20heaviest%20known%20neutron%20star%20and%20the%20lightest%20known%20black%20hole.%20That%20range%20contains%20very%20few%20objects%2C%20and%20little%20is%20known%20about%20their%20characteristics%20or%20how%20they%20could%20develop.%20Named%20GW230529%2C%20the%20signal%20was%20first%20caught%20by%20the%20researchers%20in%20May%202023.%20It%20also%20happened%20to%20be%20the%20first%20time%20when%20gravitational%20waves%20were%20used%20to%20find%20an%20object.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeraint%20Pratten%2C%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Birmingham%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20could%20not%20determine%20with%20certainty%20if%20the%20compact%20objects%20are%20black%20holes%20or%20neutron%20stars%2C%20as%20the%20gravitational%20wave%20signal%20does%20not%20provide%20enough%20information.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20very%20likely%20that%20this%20was%20the%20merger%20between%20a%20black%20hole%20and%20a%20neutron%20star.%20Either%20way%2C%20we%20are%20very%20confident%20that%20the%20heavier%20object%20falls%20within%20the%20mass%20gap%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20the%20Independent.%20The%20researcher%20concluded%20by%20saying%20the%20ongoing%20analysis%20of%20the%20phenomenon%20was%20helping%20him%20and%20other%20fellow%20scientists%20to%20have%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Castrophysical%20processes%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712469420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-02%2Fnasa-gravitational-waves_650x400_81455272328.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-detect-extremely-exciting-signal-from-unknown-celestial-body-5391530%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20new%20intergalactic%20discovery%2C%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20exciting%26quot%3B%20gravitational-wave%20signal%20has%20been%20detected%20by%20scientists%20from%20the%20far%20side%20of%20the%20universe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-detect-extremely-exciting-signal-from-unknown-celestial-body-5391530%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-detect-extremely-exciting-signal-from-unknown-celestial-body-5391530%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fscientists-detect-extremely-exciting-signal-from-unknown-celestial-body-5391530%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Witness%20'planetary%20parade'%20on%20Monday's%20solar%20eclipse%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712468895000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109101373%2Cimgsize-418893.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwitness-planetary-parade-among-other-things-during-mondays-total-solar-eclipse%2Farticleshow%2F109101306.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20April%208%2C%20a%20solar%20eclipse%20will%20darken%20certain%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20providing%20a%20rare%20view%20of%20daytime%20darkness%20and%20the%20sun's%20corona%20for%20those%20in%20its%20path.%20Observers%20will%20be%20treated%20to%20a%20unique%20'planetary%20parade'%20as%20